            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": false,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* $9 billion for the NASA Science Mission Directorate (SMD) restores American leadership in space science following the workforce and mission disruptions caused by the FY 2026 funding cuts.\n* Advancing space science is a fundamental public responsibility codified in Title 51; it secures U.S. economic competitiveness and sets the norms for 21st-century exploration against rapid expansion by China.\n* Every dollar invested in NASA returns approximately $3 to the economy, driving demand for a high-tech industrial workforce and cutting-edge R&D that no private entity can replicate.\n* SMD's peer-reviewed Decadal Surveys provide a rigorous, nonpartisan roadmap for scientific discovery, ensuring taxpayer investments are concentrated on high-priority, transformative missions.",
            "rationale": "Justification uses strategic advocacy talking points regarding U.S. leadership, competition with China, economic return on investment, and the authority of the Decadal Surveys. It references the $9 billion ask and the context of FY 2026 funding restoration.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
