            "label": "Relevance to Idaho:",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": false,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* NASA Science has obligated over $8.08 million to Idaho institutions between FY 2023 and FY 2025, supporting high-tech research and STEM employment across the state.\n* Boise State University received over $5.4 million in grant funding, including a $503,493 award for strategic science supporting lunar exploration, Mars missions, and space defense.\n* The University of Idaho leads critical research in planetary and Earth science, including a $664,543 award for global fire mapping and a $552,119 award to develop imaging for mapping molten lava.\n* Small businesses in Idaho benefit from NASA contracts, including Quality Thermistor, Inc. and McAllister Technical Services, Inc., which provide specialized technical components for agency missions.",
            "rationale": "Cites specific local spending data for Idaho, including the $8.08M total. It highlights top grant recipients Boise State University ($5.4M) and University of Idaho ($4.6M) and mentions specific active project values and goals. It also references local contract recipients.",
